<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="179" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,287,836,861]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Biology</emphasis>
. This species is found in sap-rich breeding sites in 
<taxonomicName box="[870,1098,836,861]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diversifolia">
<emphasis box="[870,1098,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Populus diversifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
trees; the larva and puparium of 
<taxonomicName box="[183,268,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="naja">
<emphasis box="[183,268,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">C. naja</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are described (
<bibRefCitation author="Krivosheina" box="[444,652,871,896]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" refString="Krivosheina, M. G. (2001) To the biology of the xylophilous flies of the genus Ceriana Rafinesque, 1815 (Diptera: Syrphidae) with the redescriptions of the larvae and puparia of C. caesarea Stackelberg and C. naja Violovitsh. International Journal of Dipterology, 12, 57 - 64." type="journal article" year="2001">Krivosheina 2001</bibRefCitation>
). Adults fly from mid April to mid August. Adults have been found visiting flowers of 
<taxonomicName box="[363,455,909,932]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tamaricaceae" genus="Tamarix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[363,455,909,932]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Tamarix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
